# Test node-style subpath imports: '#'-prefixed imports mapped by the
# package.json 'imports' field of the importing package.
# https://nodejs.org/api/packages.html#subpath-imports
#
#  * '#sub' mapping to a file generated by another Bazel package resolves
#    to that target (lib/pkg/index.ts -> //lib/pkg/sub)
#  * '#self' mapping to a file within the same target resolves to nothing
#    (lib/pkg/self.ts)
#  * '#ext' mapping to an external package resolves to the linked package
#    (lib/pkg/index.ts -> :node_modules/@lib/other)
#  * '#cond' conditionally mapping to separate directories per condition
#    ('node', 'browser', 'default') resolves to all mapped targets
#    (lib/pkg/index.ts -> //lib/pkg/cond_node + cond_browser + cond_default)
#  * the npm_package picks up targets generating internal 'imports' files
#    (//lib/pkg/sub in //lib/pkg:pkg srcs)
workspace(name = "pnpm_workspace_imports")
